    {
      "id": "9cfbcef4_97b7565c",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/common/logConfiguration/templates/_log.tpl",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 35,
      "message": "Today, in all our common templates we have this pattern:\nvalue: lowest priority, set per chart\nglobal.value: medium priority, set globally\nvalueOverride: highest priority, set per chart\n\nHere, I've decided (but it's subject to discussion ;) ) to replicate the pattern but inside the template. So, let's say I want to change the default pattern for SDNC, I'll put in its values:\n\nlogConfiguration:\n  logLevel: TRACE\n\nthen only SDNC would have per default TRACE (if nothing is set globally) and the rest would stick INFO\nBut It would still be able to force global and also overrides.\n\nIs it OK for you?\n\nThis is also why I've put \"INFO\" as default \"local\" (and not global) value",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2319,
        "name": "Sylvain Desbureaux",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "sylvain.desbureaux@orange.com",
        "username": "sdesbure"
      },
      "updated": "2020-07-22 12:23:33.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "4f9e783b_70b6a748",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
